cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fundamental problems on graphs and proposes novel techniques for fast exact shortest distance query answering. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of an auxiliary data structure (landmark covers) for shortest distance queries. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are possible categories as the paper deals with graph-based algorithms and optimization techniques. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper focuses on road graphs and their properties.
